      "content": "but diet and sleep don't explain the timing. i've been noticing it specifically after those clear nights when the aurora is visible or when there's high solar activity. it feels way more precise than just \"feeling good.\" like, it's almost a physical sensation in my head, a sort of clarity that comes from being \"aligned\" with that energy. if cosmic rays can cause mutations over long periods, could there be a way they trigger rapid epigenetic shifts in certain sensitive individuals? like a sudden upgrade to the way my DNA handles neural plasticity?",
